    <note>Zhang Hong [8013] His great great grandfather, Maozhao [3154], first appears in 791 as prefect of Dingzhou, rises to Tang military governor (Jiedu shi) of Yiwu (Izhou and Dingzhou) or Northern Hebei in 793, and was concurrently appointed Chief minister in 805. In 810, shortly before he died, he was made military governor of Hezhong, Ci, Xi, Pingyang and Jiang prefectures, most of Southwestern Shanxi. Maozhao's younger brothers, Maozong [3156] and Maohe [3155], were also Tang military officials respectively in 797 and 817. Hong was the father of Kejiu [249] and grandfather of Liang(1) Shi's [1137] daughter-in-law. QTW, 105.13b-17b; SHY:SH, 49.5a-5b, 5b-6a; SS, 267.1a-2b; ZZTJ, 233.7524, 7540, 235.7562, 7577, 237.7637, 238.7679, 7680, 240.7738. Bernard S. Solomon (trans), The Veritable Record of the Tang Emperor Shun-Tsung (Cambridge: Harvard University Press, 1955), p.6. CBD, 3, 2235-6.</note>
